{"title":"2025 Sea Otter Classic: Chris Killer Designs – Killer Drop Hardtail – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/chris-killer-designs-killer-drop/","date":1744887636000,"content":"<p><em><i>We’ve saved perhaps the most interesting </i><i><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/search/2025+Sea+Otter+Classic/\" target=\"_blank\">2025 Sea Otter Classic</a></i><i> find for last. John bumped into Chris, who was rolling his “Killer Drop” hardtail around. This unique bike allows the rider to alter the seat angle, saddle height, and pitch by using simple dropper post actuation.</i> Let’s check it out…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://1up-usa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">1UP USA</a> for sponsoring our Sea Otter Classic coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-16.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-16.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-16.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-16.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Killer Drop Story</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://killerdrop.bike/\" target=\"_blank\">Chris Killer</a> is a mechanical design engineer based in Costa Mesa, California, just outside of the city of Laguna Beach, where he loves to ride in the San Joaquin Hills. Speaking with a strong UK accent, he gave me the rundown on this unique design. Living in Southern California, the riding is very steep, both up and down. Within these local rides, Chris came up with the concept for the Killer Drop. But it wasn’t until he was stranded in China during the COVID-19 pandemic that he was able to spend a few weeks sketching out the design with SolidWorks. Once he was able to return home, he got to work on the concept.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-SLIDE-2.gif?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-SLIDE-2.gif?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-SLIDE-2.gif?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-SLIDE-2.gif?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The bike you see here is prototype number two. With one press of the dropper post lever, the Killer Drop adjusts saddle height/pitch and effective seat tube angle. It does so by activating a tension bar that is attached just below the head of the dropper post via a stanchion clamp.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-12.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-12.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-12.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Functionality</h3>\n<p>The system pivots on two spring roll pins, one near the head tube and one at the seat tube. Chris fillet brazed the frame himself, noting that he’s not a frambuilder by practice but needed a proof of concept. The entire frame is 4130 steel, but the downtube is Columbus Zona to save on weight. All in, the frame and tension bar arm weigh around 5.4 lbs or 2.45 kg. The tension bar spec is customizable to achieve the ideal drop and saddle height for the rider, too.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-15.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-15.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-15.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-15.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-1.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-1.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2024/08/2024-MADE-Bike-Show-BTCHN-Geo-Shift-MTB-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em>You might recall Tyler from <a href=\"https://www.btchnbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">BTCHN’s 2024 MADE show bike</a>, dubbed the “Geo Shift”, which uses a different mechanism for altering the bike’s effective seat tube angle.</em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-4.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Chris noted that for big, long climbs, he’ll have the saddle all the way up, but for more traversy terrain, he’ll drop it a few centimeters to allow for a slightly slacker seat angle and less forward climbing position.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-24.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-24.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-27.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-27.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-27.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-27.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Frame Details</h3>\n<p>While it’s easy to get distracted by the Killer Drop system, Chris’ ingenuity is present in other areas of the bike. Like his rear flat mount brake design, where the tube gusset passes through the stays.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-23.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-23.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-23.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>There’s also a chainstay yoke to achieve the tire clearance Chris wanted on the frame. As you can see, there’s plenty of room with the 2.4″ Maxxis Minion DHR II 29er tire.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-28a.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-28a.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-28a.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/2025-Sea-Otter-Chris-Killer-Designs-Killer-Drop-Seat-Angle-Adjust-Bike-28a.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Future Plans</h3>\n<p>Chris has no intention of making these for customers, but he would like to license the patented design to a framebuilder or company, so if you’re interested, <em>drop</em> <a href=\"https://killerdrop.bike/\" target=\"_blank\">him an email</a>.</p>\n<p>Pushing paradigms isn’t always perfect. Yet these experimental moments, often initiated by small shops or framebuilders, cause pause and reflection.</p>\n<p>So, what do you think of the Killer Drop? Let us and Chris know in the comments!</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/04/SeaOtter_1UP_USA_Coverage.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://1up-usa.com/\" target=\"_blank\">1UP USA</a> for sponsoring our Sea Otter Classic coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/chris-killer-designs-killer-drop/\">2025 Sea Otter Classic: Chris Killer Designs – Killer Drop Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"e56598443e92de1bacab4b5e7f57030278c6c4f3cb3236b384c9bb2071ea4eed","category":"Cycling"}